              corresp="#rafi0005.diplomatic #rafi0005.translation">
            <p>
               <unclear>εἵς</unclear>
               <choice>
                  <abbr>
                     <unclear>θς</unclear>
                  </abbr>
                  <expan>θεός</expan>
               </choice> Κυρ<unclear>ι Σ</unclear>ερη...
                </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:id="rafi0005.translation"
              corresp="#rafi0005.diplomatic #rafi0005.transcription">
            <p>[There is] one God. Kuri(?) Sere(?)</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The opening "[There is] one God..." (usually followed by "who helps") is a Christian formula common throughout the region and era. The attested names most resembling those here are Σερηυ and Κουρι, Κύρις, Κύρες, and Κύρος. Dimensions refer to entire remainder of stone.</p>
         </div>
